eter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Deep science content knowledge needed for independent curriculum planning and guiding hands-on inquiry for young learners.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Pedagogical Planning and Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 8</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Essential for designing and delivering engaging, NGSS-aligned, inquiry-based science lessons and projects.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Classroom Management and Culture</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Supports a positive, inclusive, and collaborative classroom needed for hands-on labs and group learning activities.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Assessment and Data-Driven Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Needed to measure student growth, adjust instruction, and provide timely feedback as outlined in responsibilities.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Differentiation and Inclusive Practices</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Accommodating diverse needs is essential for inclusion and personalized science learning at this new school.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Technology-Enhanced Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Facilitates STEAM integration, digital science resources, and potential use of EdTech in new school setting.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Curriculum Development and Standards Alignment</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 8</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Critical for developing a new NGSS-aligned science program and integrating K-8 curriculum from scratch.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Collaboration and Professionalism</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Vital as a founding teacher for collaborative team design, faculty events, and interdisciplinary projects.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Communication and Family Engagement</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Ongoing parent updates and partnership are expected for student progress and class events.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Student SEL and Wellbeing</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Contributes to a supportive, community-driven culture; part of whole-child focus articulated in school’s vision.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Culturally Responsive Teaching</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">School community values inclusion and diversity; position expects commitment to equity in learning.</div></div></div></div></div><div class="card ana"><h2>Detailed Analysis</h2><div class="section"><div><strong>Role Snapshot:</strong><ul><li>Founding full-time science teacher, grades 2–5</li><li>New K–8 charter school, opens fall 2024</li><li>Inquiry-based, STEAM-focused instructional model</li><li>Collaborative and community-centered team</li></ul></div><div><strong>Core Responsibilities:</strong><ul><li>Design and deliver NGSS-aligned science curriculum</li><li>Lead hands-on labs, projects, and outdoor learning</li><li>Assess growth and provide individualized support</li><li>Facilitate interdisciplinary science initiatives</li><li>Engage in ongoing professional development</li></ul></div><div><strong>Student Needs & Differentiation:</strong><ul><li>Differentiate instruction for diverse learning needs</li><li>Personalize support and scaffolds for student growth</li><li>Foster inclusion and equitable participation</li></ul></div><div><strong>Collaboration & Communication:</strong><ul><li>Partner with colleagues for lesson planning</li><li>Communicate with parents/families regularly</li><li>Participate in faculty teams and school events</li></ul></div><div><strong>Technology Expectations:</strong><ul><li>Integrate digital tools as part of STEAM curriculum</li><li>Leverage EdTech for science instruction</li></ul></div><div><strong>Other Notes:</strong><ul><li>Start date: August 15, 2024</li><li>Mentorship and professional growth offered</li><li>Contact: principal@crestviewacademy.org, (254) 555-1379</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>', N'{
