;padding:10px;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.6fr .8fr .8fr 2fr;gap:10px;align-items:center}.req-name{font-weight:600}.level{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px}.meter{height:8px;background:#eef1f7;border-radius:6px;position:relative;overflow:hidden}.meter .fill{position:absolute;left:0;top:0;height:100%;border-radius:6px}.fill.min{background:linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(43,92,255,.35),rgba(43,92,255,.55))}.fill.target{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--accent),#11c997)}.lvl-label{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted)}.just{font-size:13px;color:var(--ink)}.tags{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-top:6px}.tag{background:#f0f3fa;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:4px 8px;color:#2b3a55;font-size:12px}.ana ul{margin:0;padding-left:18px}.ana li{margin:4px 0}.section{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px}.muted{color:var(--muted)}</style></head><body><div class="wrap"><div class="hero"><h1><span class="schoolName">Harmony Ridge Elementary School</span> — <span class="position">Middle School Teacher</span></h1><div class="meta"><span class="chip gradeLevels">Grades: 6-8</span><span class="chip exp">Desired Experience: 7+ years</span><span class="chip contact">careers@harmonyridgeesd.org | (619) 555-3456 | 425 Willow Valley Dr., San Diego, CA</span></div><div class="summary"><strong>Brief:</strong> <span class="briefSummary">Full-time middle school teaching role (grades 6–8) in a bilingual, inclusive setting. 7+ years’ experience and Spanish proficiency strongly preferred. Diverse curriculum, high collaboration, strong classroom management.</span></div></div><div class="grid"><div class="card"><h2>Key Requirements</h2><div class="section"><div class="tags muted">Ratings: 1 (low) to 10 (high). Calibrated conservatively.</div><div class="req-table"><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Curriculum Development and Standards Alignment</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 8</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Required to plan and deliver lessons for several core subjects and grade levels, ensuring alignment with standards and robust student outcomes.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Subject-Matter Expertise (Middle School Core)</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 8</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Teachers cover language arts, math, science, and social studies for grades 6–8, requiring strong core content mastery across subjects.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Differentiation and Inclusive Practices</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Experience with differentiated instruction and inclusive education is crucial for meeting the needs of a diverse student community.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Assessment and Data-Driven Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">The role requires regular monitoring, record-keeping, and providing actionable feedback based on student progress in multiple subjects.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Pedagogical Planning and Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 8</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">High expectations for planning, implementing, and adjusting instruction to engage and support diverse classes in grades 6–8.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Communication and Family Engagement</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Frequent engagement with families and bilingual communication (English/Spanish) is strongly preferred to support student growth.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Subject-Matter Expertise (Science)</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Science is among the core subjects taught; demonstrated knowledge enables engaging and meaningful instruction.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Collaboration and Professionalism</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Teacher is expected to work closely with teams, attend meetings, share practices, and participate in school-wide PD and events.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Classroom Management and Culture</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 8</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Strong classroom management is required to create a positive, inclusive, and academically focused culture for middle schoolers.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Technology-Enhanced Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 3</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 30%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Although not tech-centric, teachers are expected to use basic educational technology and electronic record-keeping platforms.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Culturally Responsive Teaching</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Serving a bilingual, diverse student population requires sensitivity to culture and language in pedagogy and expectations.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Student SEL and Wellbeing</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">SEL is implied in school values of respect and kindness; supporting wellbeing is key to fostering student success and engagement.</div></div></div></div></div><div class="card ana"><h2>Detailed Analysis</h2><div class="section"><div><strong>Role Snapshot:</strong><ul><li>Full-time position for grades 6–8</li><li>Core subjects: language arts, math, science, social studies</li><li>Bilingual, inclusive school community</li><li>Start date: August 12, 2024</li></ul></div><div><strong>Core Responsibilities:</strong><ul><li>Plan and deliver standards-aligned curriculum for multiple subjects</li><li>Implement diverse instructional strategies for all learners</li><li>Assess and document student performance</li><li>Model school values in classroom and community</li><li>Engage in professional development and staff meetings</li></ul></div><div><strong>Student Needs & Differentiation:</strong><ul><li>Differentiated instruction for multilingual, multicultural students</li><li>Inclusive practices for varied learning needs</li><li>Maintain a positive, respectful classroom culture</li></ul></div><div><strong>Collaboration & Communication:</strong><ul><li>Communicate with families, students, and colleagues—often bilingually</li><li>Collaborate with grade-level teams and specialists</li></ul></div><div><strong>Technology Expectations:</strong><ul><li>Utilize digital tools for planning, instruction, and record-keeping</li><li>Engage with electronic communication and reporting platforms</li></ul></div><div><strong>Other Notes:</strong><ul><li>Minimum 7 years teaching experience required</li><li>California teaching credential is mandatory</li><li>Spanish proficiency strongly preferred</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>', N'{
