</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 9</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 90%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Role requires deep content knowledge, especially in AP/advanced math, to teach upper-level courses and mentor colleagues.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Pedagogical Planning and Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 8</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Must plan and deliver rigorous lessons in advanced math, modeling best practice for department faculty.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Curriculum Development and Standards Alignment</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 8</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Charged with developing and aligning the department curriculum to state standards and college-readiness benchmarks.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Assessment and Data-Driven Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Expected to monitor/analyze student data to improve department and individual instruction.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Collaboration and Professionalism</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 8</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Must supervise, coach, and develop math teachers, lead meetings, and collaborate with administration.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Classroom Management and Culture</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Maintains a positive, motivating classroom and department culture to foster student enthusiasm for math.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Differentiation and Inclusive Practices</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Charged with ensuring equitable and effective instruction for diverse learners in advanced math settings.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Communication and Family Engagement</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Regularly communicates with students, families, and stakeholders about progress, expectations, and programs.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Technology-Enhanced Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Incorporates technology for math instruction and is familiar with tech integration; not central but included.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Student SEL and Wellbeing</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Supports a positive environment for student growth and resilience in challenging advanced math courses.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Culturally Responsive Teaching</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Commitment to diversity, equity, and inclusion in teaching and departmental leadership is expected.</div></div></div></div></div><div class="card ana"><h2>Detailed Analysis</h2><div class="section"><div><strong>Role Snapshot:</strong><ul><li>Full-time department head for Mathematics, teaching 9–12 (AP/advanced focus).</li><li>Leads and mentors a team of 6 math teachers.</li><li>Oversees curriculum and instructional quality across department.</li><li>Teaches 2–3 sections of advanced mathematics.</li><li>10-month contract, starts August 15, 2024.</li></ul></div><div><strong>Core Responsibilities:</strong><ul><li>Lead instructional practices and professional development for HS math.</li><li>Supervise and mentor other math teachers.</li><li>Curriculum oversight and alignment with state/college standards.</li><li>Teach advanced math/AP Calculus sections.</li><li>Data monitoring and improving math outcomes.</li><li>Facilitate math competitions and bridge programs.</li><li>Engage families about course/program progress.</li></ul></div><div><strong>Student Needs & Differentiation:</strong><ul><li>Ensure curriculum meets diverse learners’ needs in advanced math settings.</li><li>Advocate for equity, access, and inclusion in math instruction.</li><li>Use and model differentiation strategies for all learners.</li></ul></div><div><strong>Collaboration & Communication:</strong><ul><li>Partner with admin to set and implement department goals.</li><li>Lead and coordinate department meetings & PD workshops.</li><li>Maintain regular, responsive family communications.</li></ul></div><div><strong>Technology Expectations:</strong><ul><li>Expect familiarity with tech integration in math classrooms.</li><li>Potential for using LMS and data tools as part of instruction and oversight.</li></ul></div><div><strong>Other Notes:</strong><ul><li>Salary $62,000–$88,000 depending on experience.</li><li>Location: 1234 Main St, Springfield, USA.</li><li>Extensive health and retirement benefits offered.</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>', N'{
